<title type="html"><![CDATA[12/22 (Thu)K-Pop: The Rise of the Virtual Girl Bands/The 2022 Chemistry Nobel Prize Winner (Host: George)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=682&amp;p=710#p710"><![CDATA[
12/22 (Thu)K-Pop: The Rise of the Virtual Girl Bands/The 2022 Chemistry Nobel Prize Winner (Host: George)<br /><br />Agenda:<br />7:00-7:10 pm Opening Remarks<br />7:05-7:40 pm Session 1: Group Discussion<br />7:40-8:00 pm Individual Presentation<br />8:00-8:05 pm Break<br />8:05-8:40 pm Session 2: Group Discussion<br />8:40-9:00 pm Individual Presentation<br /><br />We will hold a zoom meeting only.<br /><br />Zoom meeting: Please click the link below<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://zoomtw.zoom.us/j/92987266213?pw">https://zoomtw.zoom.us/j/92987266213?pw</a><!-- m --> ...<br />Meeting ID:929 8726 6213<br />Password:112233<br /><br />--------------------------------------------<br /><br />Session1: 12/22 (Thu)K-Pop: The Rise of the Virtual Girl Bands<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-63827838">https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-63827838</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Questions:<br />1.K-pop becomes famous in the world in recent years. Do you know any K-pop idols or artists?<br />2.Have you ever heard the virtual artists/idols? What are your thoughts?<br />3.As we know that K-pop stars often struggle with physical limitations or even mental distress. Do you think that virtual artists/idols can replace actual artists?<br />4.The pandemic helps virtual artists/idols become more and more popular. Do you think that virtual artists/idols are still popular since the pandemic ends?<br />5.Please share your favorite idols. What were the craziest things that you did to your favorite idols?<br /><br /><br />Session 2: Click Chemistry and Bioorthogonality Win the 2022 Nobel Prize in Chemistry<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://bigthink.com/hard-science/2022-nobel-prize-chemistry/">https://bigthink.com/hard-science/2022- ... chemistry/</a><!-- m --><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_u7ToGXWINU">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_u7ToGXWINU</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Mr.Sharpless won his second Noble Prize in his life, and now is the fifth person that wins Nobles twice.<br />1.Have you ever awarded the prize in your school life? Please share your story.<br />2.Are sciences your favorite subjects? What was your favorite subject when you were student?<br />3.Do you ever hear “Click Chemistry”? How can this new method change our life?<br />4.The pandemic helps the pharmaceutical companies and techniques grow intensely. Do you think that it is appropriate to against the natural selection(物競天擇)?<br /><br /><br />P.S.<br />1.參加三次(含實體及線上會議)後，只要繳交1,000元(學生500元)，即可成為ROYAL終身會員!<br />2.請帶著開放的心與熱情來參加全英文會話聚會!<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38674">Louie Wang</a> — Sun Dec 18, 2022 12:14 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
